OL,6,FDet Ch Insp Smith added: "There is
OL,7,Fzero justification for the course of
OL,8,Fevents which led to Bradley's death,
OL,9,Fand Gavin Train's decision to arm
OL,10,Fhimself that night has unfortunately
OL,11,Fhad fatal consequences.
OL,13,F"That decision to carry a weapon is
OL,14,Fthe reason Bradley is no longer with
OL,15,Fus, and as a Force this case once
OL,16,Fagain reflects our clear message to
OL,17,Fthose who carry knives and choose to
OL,18,Finvolve themselves in violence.
